<TITLE> 'Motivation committee' to tackle militancy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka , Apr 22 (bdnews24.com)The government has formed a high-level 'motivation committee' to beef up intelligence surveillance and raise public awareness in tackling militancy, a government official said Wednesday. "A 17-member committee has been constituted with the state minister for home at the helm," joint secretary (political) to the home ministry Md Nurun Nabi Talukdar told bdnews24.com It includes secretaries from the prime minister's office, home, education, law, religion, social affairs, information and local government ministries. Other members of the committee include the inspector general of police, chiefs of DGFI, NSI, BDR, RAB ansar and VDP. "Apart from tackling militancy, the committee will address law and order related issues," said Talukdar. An official at the home ministry told bdnews24.com the latter involved informing authorities of any attempts to provoke social unrest among other things. The home minister issued a gazette notification signed by the joint secretary in this regard on Monday. bdnews
